        "_account_id": 8,
        "name": "zhen liang",
        "email": "liang.zhen@live.com",
        "username": "liang"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-01 03:38:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (2 inline comments)\n\nChris,\nThanks for posting this patch, it's generally good, just one concern:\nwe probably will see tons of complain that upgraded system reject connecting request from old version, even we put this in changelog and upgrading notes. \n\nHow do you think if we:\n- always use privileged port for active connecting\n- the tunable is only for passive side, and it's disabled by default (so it still can accept connecting request from non-privileged port by default), this will give user a friendly choice, and we can turn this on by default in longer future after everyone starting to actively connect via privileged port.\n\nThanks\nLiang",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
